[4] Germany: case recovering
Date: Thu 28 Aug 2014
Source: NDR.de [edited]
http://www.ndr.de/nachrichten/hamburg/Hamburger-UKE-behandelt-Ebola-Patienten,ebola150.html [in German, summary submitted by contributor]


The medical doctor from Senegal who has acquired an ebolavirus infection in Sierra Leone was transported to Germany yesterday [27 Aug 2014] where he is currently being treated at the University Hospital in Hamburg. According to media reports and the treating physicians, he is in stable condition at the moment. On the website, there is also a video showing the patient walking on his own out of the airplane at Hamburg airport.

